{
  "stem": "27509.9",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Then one of the stumbling blocks for any thinking man must be the Holocaust, because you-- you have to come to terms about human nature, which we have always thought to be the-- the crown of God's creation.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And yet, it's turning out to be, at times, somewhat less than that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Why did I want to tell my story?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, I told my story, first of all, because of private pressures of the family.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I told my story because it was-- the-- the experiences in Europe were widely, widely recorded.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Precisely because my-- my experiences were, in terms of tragedy, of a secondary nature-- I was the lucky one.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But historically, they ought to have-- to be recorded just the same, I thought, because it affected, not me.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It affected thousands of people, and to give some sort of equilibrium to the disequilibrium of-- of the Shoah in Europe, to the negation or overlooking of everything else.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then, of course, I was mindful about my 40-years life and-- and activity in Australia, and the things that I-- I was fortunate enough to be able to create, and-- and I'm still doing, because as you know, I'm the chairman of the Committee for [NON-ENGLISH] Jewish Studies.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we're now building university departments at Monash and at Melbourne, and maintaining, and so on.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I haven't finished yet.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I haven't finished yet.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "As long as one is alive and one is-- half a brain is working, we are doing.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "There's plenty to do, and not enough people to do it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But there's still plenty, plenty to do, plenty.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
